description_en: The photo capture speed, or "click-to-click time" with which one can take consecutive photographs is a critical component of photography. The primary factors affecting the capture speed are the speed of the camera processor and the write speed of the digital film (the time it takes to store an image to the digital film). As cameras with faster processing capabilities appear in the market, the sustained write capabilities of digital film will be the key metric for evaluating digital film speed. With advances in photo-resolution and the corresponding larger memory requirements, the speed with which film can write, and subsequently stored, will become increasingly more important.    Lexar Media CompactFlash cards come in a variety of sizes making it easier for you to find the capacity that best suits your personal needs and best matches your camera's capabilities. No more worrying about whether your memory cards will work in your CompactFlash digital camera. All Lexar Media CompactFlash cards are 100% guaranteed to be compatible with your CompactFlash camera. Each Lexar Media CompactFlash card adheres to the specifications established by the CompactFlash Association. This is further assurance that your Lexar Media CompactFlash card will be compatible with digital cameras and other devices that accept CompactFlash cards.

description_en: Maximize your digital file storage with the durable MSX-512S Memory Stick PRO media from Sony. Featuring 512 megabytes of storage space with 460 megabytes available and an expanded operating temperature range of -13° F to 185° Fahrenheit, you get all of the benefits of standard Memory Stick PRO media with increased durability.    The MSX-512S is backwards compatible with most devices that use standard Memory Stick PRO media. Its compact design is slightly smaller than a stick of chewing gum, so it's incredibly compact and very easy to store. Its combination of storage size, durability and compatibility makes it the perfect complement to a new digital camera.
description_fr: La nouvelle gamme de supports Memory Stick PRO standard bénéficie de la même durabilité que la version haut débit, fonctionne sous une plage de température plus large que ses prédécesseurs (de -25° C à 85° C au lieu de 0° C à 60° C). Le nouveau Memory Stick PRO 512 Mo est une solution abordable pour les utilisateurs voulant bénéficier d'une mémoire haute capacité. Il fonctionne avec toute une gamme d'applications, notamment les enregistreurs audio MP3, les caméscopes et les ordinateurs Sony équipés d'un lecteur Memory Stick. Le Memory Stick PRO est doté de MagicGate, un logiciel de protection des droits d'auteur qui utilise des technologies d'authentification et de cryptage. Sa vitesse maximale de transfert est en théorie de 160 Mbit/s (20 Mo/s) avec une vitesse d'écriture minimale de 15 Mbit/s pour assurer un enregistrement vidéo de haute qualité, en temps réel. Le Memory Stick PRO représente une solution évolutive, tournée vers l'avenir, et donc capable de répondre aux besoins changeants des utilisateurs et aux exigences des nouvelles applications.

description_en: Today's professional digital cameras capture the highest resolution images ever, at lightning-fast speeds. The large image files they produce, however, can load your camera's buffer and ultimately make you wait to take the next picture. Also, you cannot view what you've shot until the images are stored to the digital film. For the professional shooter who needs immediate confirmation they've captured "the shot" or wants to identify accurate exposure, levels, or bracketing range - Lexar Media's patented technology is critical. Ideal for fast-paced applications such as photojournalism, sports and fashion, Lexar's Professional media brings out the ultimate performance from your professional equipment.    Lexar Media's USB-enabled CompactFlash cards are specifically designed for use with the Lexar JumpShot cable, which provides a high-speed, easy-to-use connection to your PC or Mac system via your computer's USB port. USB-enabled CompactFlash cards are also backwards compatible for use in any other CompactFlash reader.

description_en: Monster Camcorder PowerCells feature protective circuitry that monitors the battery's power level as it's charged. This safeguards your PowerCell from being over-or under-charged, so it delivers full power each time when properly charged.    Whether it's for business or pleasure, on the road or at home, Monster is proud to help you express your creativity and help you capture, and save, more Monsterous memories.    Why be caught short of power? There's no missing the action, or a great scene, and no waiting, when you keep a second Powercell fully charged and ready to go.    Monster InfoCell circuitry helps track battery power level. Your camcorder can then accurately display, in minutes, how much usage time remains. Monster makes sure you know you've got the juice you need to capture the footage you want!
